  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "A shattered force of Iron Hands under Captain Durun Atticus, with Salamander and Raven Guard survivors of Isstvan V grafted onto its command, makes planetfall on the death world Pythos and tries to turn it into a base from which to wage an independent war on Horus. The jungle answers with predators that should not exist; a stream of human refugees fleeing the war washes up on the same shore; and the astropath Rhydia Erephren slowly works out that Pythos is not just hostile — it is a wound, a warp-touched site Atticus's rage will not let him abandon. Through the Salamander Khi'dem, the Iron Hand Galba, Erephren and Atticus himself, the novel watches a small Imperial enclave argue itself into damnation while the planet feeds.",
